						               													<description>This is the fourth game in the series of &amp;quot;Scarlet Envelope&amp;quot; games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;The death of Janice Ward, a young mother of two and a waitress at Stanley&amp;rsquo;s Diner, is being investigated in connection to similar cases in the state...&amp;rdquo; In this murder mystery game, you work as a cop in the fifties. Bring justice to the victims of a serial killer who clearly has a thing for junk food and pretty waitresses! Expect an escape room in an envelope full of case files, evidence bags, coroner&amp;rsquo;s reports, and lots of digital interaction. You will unlock audio-interviews and video footage of suspects&amp;rsquo; interrogations (with real actors!), and if you solve all puzzles and connect all dots, you will catch the killer yourself!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GAME CONTENTS:&amp;#10;- Videos of suspects&amp;rsquo; interrogations&amp;#10;- Audio interviews with witnesses&amp;#10;- Coroner&amp;rsquo;s report&amp;#10;- Investigation report&amp;#10;- Vintage Diner&amp;rsquo;s menu&amp;#10;- Cryptic notes left by the serial killer&amp;#10;- Three plastic evidence bags with extra items to investigate&amp;#10;- Website pages with digital items&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game really puts your detective skills to the test! The gameplay is full of puzzles but is focused on the investigation. All the puzzles are crucial to access locked items and gather enough information to put the right suspect behind the bars. Roughly 2 hours of gameplay. Two levels of difficulty available.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Parental Advisory: Mild Content (chilling but no bloody visuals.)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game is a part of the Scarlet Envelope series of games. You can play them all in any order.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
